# Use Astro Image Component

Always use the `Image` component from `astro:assets` to display images. Never use plain `<img>` tags.

```astro
---
// ❌ BAD
---
<img src="/photos/hero.jpg" alt="Hero" />
<img src={myImage} alt="Hero" />

---
// ✅ GOOD
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import heroImg from '@/assets/hero.jpg';
---
<Image src={heroImg} alt="Hero" />
```

- Import `Image` from `astro:assets` in the frontmatter
- Import local images as ESM imports so Astro can optimise them
- For remote images, configure `image.domains` or `image.remotePatterns` in `astro.config.*` and pass the URL string as `src`
- Always provide a meaningful `alt` attribute
